===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|skyn}}, {{m|enm|skinn}}, from {{inh|en|ang|scinn}}, from {{der|en|non|skinn|t=animal hide}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*skinþą}} (compare {{cog|nl|schinde||bark}}, dialectal German {{m|de|Schinde||fruit peel}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|*sken-|t=to split off}} (compare {{cog|br|skant||scales}}, {{cog|sga|ceinn}}, {{cog|ga|scainim||I tear, burst}}, {{cog|la|scindo|scindere|to split, divide}}, {{cog|sa|छिनत्ति|tr=chinátti||he splits}}), nasal variant of {{m|ine-pro|*skeh₁i-d-||to cut}}. Partially displaced native Old English {{m|ang|hȳd|t=skin, hide}}, see {{l|en|hide}}. More at {{l|en|shed}}.

